#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.62:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.62:0.3"
msgid "62. Purisindriyañāṇasutta"
msgstr "62. Knowledge of the Faculties of Persons"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an6.62:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an6.62:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena "
"saddhiṃ yena daṇḍakappakaṃ nāma kosalānaṃ nigamo tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together "
"with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a town of the Kosalans "
"named Daṇḍakappaka."

msgctxt "an6.62:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā maggā okkamma aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha left the road and sat at the root of a tree on the seat spread "
"out."

msgctxt "an6.62:1.4"
msgid "Te ca bhikkhū daṇḍakappakaṃ pavisiṃsu āvasathaṃ pariyesituṃ."
msgstr "The mendicants entered Daṇḍakappaka to look for a guest house."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena aciravatī nadī "
"tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda together with several mendicants went to the Aciravati "
"River to bathe."

msgctxt "an6.62:2.2"
msgid ""
"Aciravatiyā nadiyā gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi "
"gattāni pubbāpayamāno."
msgstr ""
"When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying "
"himself."

msgctxt "an6.62:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a certain mendicant went up to Venerable Ānanda, and said to him:"

msgctxt "an6.62:2.4"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso ānanda, sabbaṃ cetaso samannāharitvā nu kho devadatto "
"bhagavatā byākato:"
msgstr "“Reverend Ānanda, when the Buddha declared that Devadatta was"

msgctxt "an6.62:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti, udāhu kenacideva "
"pariyāyenāti?"
msgstr ""
"going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable, "
"did he do so after wholeheartedly deliberating, or was this just a way of "
"speaking?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā byākatan”ti."
msgstr "“You’re right, reverend, that’s how the Buddha declared it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.403"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and told him what had happened."

msgctxt "an6.62:3.2"
msgid ""
"“idhāhaṃ, bhante, sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena aciravatī nadī "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃ gattāni parisiñcituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:3.3"
msgid ""
"Aciravatiyā nadiyā gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsiṃ "
"gattāni pubbāpayamāno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:3.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, aññataro bhikkhu yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:3.5"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso ānanda, sabbaṃ cetaso samannāharitvā nu kho devadatto "
"bhagavatā byākato—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:3.6"
msgid ""
"āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekicchoti, udāhu kenacideva "
"pariyāyenā’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:3.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:3.8"
msgid "‘evaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā byākatan’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: vā → so ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.62:4.1"
msgid ""
"“So vā kho, ānanda, bhikkhu navo bhavissati acirapabbajito, thero vā pana "
"bālo abyatto."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, that mendicant must be junior, recently gone forth, or else a "
"foolish, incompetent senior mendicant."

msgctxt "an6.62:4.2"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma yaṃ mayā ekaṃsena byākataṃ tattha dvejjhaṃ āpajjissati."
msgstr ""
"How on earth can he take something that I have declared definitively to be "
"ambiguous?"

msgctxt "an6.62:4.3"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ, ānanda, aññaṃ ekapuggalampi samanupassāmi, yo evaṃ mayā sabbaṃ cetaso "
"samannāharitvā byākato, yathayidaṃ devadatto."
msgstr ""
"I do not see a single other person concerning whom I have made a declaration "
"about after giving such wholehearted deliberation as Devadatta."

msgctxt "an6.62:4.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, ānanda, devadattassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi "
"sukkadhammaṃ addasaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"As long as I saw even a fraction of a hair’s tip of goodness in Devadatta"

msgctxt "an6.62:4.5"
msgid "neva tāvāhaṃ devadattaṃ byākāsiṃ:"
msgstr "I did not declare that he was"

msgctxt "an6.62:4.6"
msgid "‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti."
msgstr ""
"going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable."

msgctxt "an6.62:4.7"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho ahaṃ, ānanda, devadattassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi "
"sukkadhammaṃ na addasaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"But when I saw that there was not even a fraction of a hair’s tip of "
"goodness in Devadatta"

msgctxt "an6.62:4.8"
msgid "athāhaṃ devadattaṃ byākāsiṃ:"
msgstr "I declared that he was"

msgctxt "an6.62:4.9"
msgid "‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti."
msgstr ""
"going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.404"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, gūthakūpo sādhikaporiso pūro gūthassa samatittiko."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a sewer deeper than a man’s height, full to the brim with "
"feces,"

msgctxt "an6.62:5.2"
msgid "Tatra puriso sasīsako nimuggo assa."
msgstr "and someone was sunk into it over their head."

msgctxt "an6.62:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya atthakāmo hitakāmo yogakkhemakāmo tamhā "
"gūthakūpā uddharitukāmo."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person who wants to help make them safe, who wants to "
"lift them out of that sewer."

msgctxt "an6.62:5.4"
msgid ""
"So taṃ gūthakūpaṃ samantānuparigacchanto neva passeyya tassa purisassa "
"vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi gūthena amakkhitaṃ, yattha taṃ gahetvā "
"uddhareyya."
msgstr ""
"But circling all around the sewer they couldn’t see even a fraction of a "
"hair’s tip on that person that was not smeared with feces."

msgctxt "an6.62:5.5"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, yato devadattassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi "
"sukkadhammaṃ na addasaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when I saw that there was not even a fraction of a hair’s "
"tip of goodness in Devadatta"

msgctxt "an6.62:5.6"
msgid "athāhaṃ devadattaṃ byākāsiṃ:"
msgstr "I declared that he was"

msgctxt "an6.62:5.7"
msgid "‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti."
msgstr ""
"going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable."

# This specific phrasing is shared with MN 136 and AN 6.62. In both cases, the context follows a case where a junior monk has made a silly statement. I think the phrasing is meant to express a certain frustration, if I may dare to use such a term of the Buddha! The parsing of vibhajantassa is problematic, see BB’s note on AN 6.62.
#. VAR: vibhajissāmī”ti → vibhajantassāti (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.62:5.8"
msgid ""
"Sace tumhe, ānanda, suṇeyyātha tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇāni "
"vibhajissāmī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, if only you would all listen to the Realized One’s analysis of the "
"knowledges of the faculties of individuals.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:6.1"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "an6.62:6.2"
msgid ""
"yaṃ bhagavā purisindriyañāṇāni vibhajeyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū "
"dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Let the Buddha analyze the faculties of persons. The mendicants will listen "
"and remember it.”"

msgctxt "an6.62:6.3"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an6.62:6.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "an6.62:6.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.405"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:7.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "“Ānanda, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.2"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.4"
msgid ""
"‘imassa kho puggalassa kusalā dhammā antarahitā, akusalā dhammā "
"sammukhībhūtā."
msgstr ""
"‘The skillful qualities of this person have vanished, but the unskillful "
"qualities are still present."

msgctxt "an6.62:7.5"
msgid ""
"Atthi ca khvassa kusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tamhā tassa kusalā kusalaṃ "
"pātubhavissati."
msgstr ""
"Nevertheless, their skillful root is unbroken, and from that the skillful "
"will appear."

msgctxt "an6.62:7.6"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ aparihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "So this person is not liable to decline in the future.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.7"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, bījāni akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sāradāni "
"sukhasayitāni sukhette suparikammakatāya bhūmiyā nikkhittāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose some seeds were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and "
"well-kept. They’re sown in a well-prepared, productive field."

msgctxt "an6.62:7.8"
msgid ""
"Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, imāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ "
"āpajjissantī”ti?"
msgstr "Wouldn’t you know that those seeds would grow, increase, and mature?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.10"
msgid ""
"“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand …"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.11"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:7.12"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:7.13"
msgid ""
"‘imassa kho puggalassa kusalā dhammā antarahitā, akusalā dhammā "
"sammukhībhūtā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:7.14"
msgid ""
"Atthi ca khvassa kusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tamhā tassa kusalā kusalaṃ "
"pātubhavissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:7.15"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ aparihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "This person is not liable to decline in the future …"

msgctxt "an6.62:7.16"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisapuggalo cetasā ceto paricca vidito "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"This is how another individual is known to the Realized One by comprehending "
"their mind."

msgctxt "an6.62:7.17"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"viditaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"And this is how the Realized One knows a person’s faculties by comprehending "
"their mind."

msgctxt "an6.62:7.18"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca "
"vidito hoti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"And this is how the Realized One knows the future origination of a person’s "
"qualities by comprehending their mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.406"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:8.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.2"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.4"
msgid ""
"‘imassa kho puggalassa akusalā dhammā antarahitā, kusalā dhammā "
"sammukhībhūtā."
msgstr ""
"‘The unskillful qualities of this person have vanished, but the skillful "
"qualities are still present."

msgctxt "an6.62:8.5"
msgid ""
"Atthi ca khvassa akusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tamhā tassa akusalā akusalaṃ "
"pātubhavissati."
msgstr ""
"Nevertheless, their unskillful root is unbroken, and from that the "
"unskillful will appear."

msgctxt "an6.62:8.6"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ parihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "So this person is still liable to decline in the future.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.7"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, bījāni akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sāradāni "
"sukhasayitāni puthusilāya nikkhittāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose some seeds were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and "
"well-kept. And they were sown on a broad rock."

msgctxt "an6.62:8.8"
msgid ""
"Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, nayimāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ "
"āpajjissantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Wouldn’t you know that those seeds would not grow, increase, and mature?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.10"
msgid ""
"“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand …"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.11"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:8.12"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:8.13"
msgid ""
"‘imassa kho puggalassa akusalā dhammā antarahitā, kusalā dhammā "
"sammukhībhūtā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:8.14"
msgid ""
"Atthi ca khvassa akusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tamhā tassa akusalā akusalaṃ "
"pātubhavissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:8.15"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ parihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "This person is still liable to decline in the future …"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.16"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisapuggalo cetasā ceto paricca vidito "
"hoti."
msgstr "This is how another individual is known to the Realized One …"

msgctxt "an6.62:8.17"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"viditaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:8.18"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca "
"vidito hoti. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:9.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.2"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.4"
msgid ""
"‘natthi imassa puggalassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattopi sukko dhammo, "
"samannāgatoyaṃ puggalo ekantakāḷakehi akusalehi dhammehi, kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person has not even a fraction of a hair’s tip of goodness. They have "
"exclusively dark, unskillful qualities. When their body breaks up, after "
"death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, "
"hell.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, bījāni khaṇḍāni pūtīni vātātapahatāni sukhette "
"suparikammakatāya bhūmiyā nikkhittāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose some seeds were broken, spoiled, weather-damaged. They’re sown in a "
"well-prepared, productive field."

msgctxt "an6.62:9.6"
msgid ""
"Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, nayimāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ "
"āpajjissantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Wouldn’t you know that those seeds would not grow, increase, and mature?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.8"
msgid ""
"“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand …"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.9"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:9.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:9.11"
msgid ""
"‘natthi imassa puggalassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattopi sukko dhammo, "
"samannāgatoyaṃ puggalo ekantakāḷakehi akusalehi dhammehi, kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person has not even a fraction of a hair’s tip of goodness. They have "
"exclusively dark, unskillful qualities. When their body breaks up, after "
"death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, "
"hell.’ …”"

msgctxt "an6.62:9.12"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisapuggalo cetasā ceto paricca vidito "
"hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:9.13"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"viditaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:9.14"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca "
"vidito hotī”ti. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.407"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.2"
msgid ""
"“sakkā nu kho, bhante, imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ aparepi tayo puggalā "
"sappaṭibhāgā paññāpetun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, can you describe three other persons who are counterparts of these "
"three?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.3"
msgid "“Sakkā, ānandā”ti bhagavā avoca:"
msgstr "“I can, Ānanda,” said the Buddha."

msgctxt "an6.62:10.4"
msgid "“idhāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "“Ānanda, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.5"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.7"
msgid ""
"‘imassa kho puggalassa kusalā dhammā antarahitā, akusalā dhammā "
"sammukhībhūtā."
msgstr ""
"‘The skillful qualities of this person have vanished, but the unskillful "
"qualities are still present."

msgctxt "an6.62:10.8"
msgid ""
"Atthi ca khvassa kusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tampi sabbena sabbaṃ samugghātaṃ "
"gacchati."
msgstr ""
"Nevertheless, their skillful root is unbroken, but it’s about to be totally "
"destroyed."

msgctxt "an6.62:10.9"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ parihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "So this person is still liable to decline in the future.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.10"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, aṅgārāni ādittāni sampajjalitāni sajotibhūtāni "
"puthusilāya nikkhittāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that there were some burning coals, blazing and glowing. And they "
"were placed on a broad rock."

msgctxt "an6.62:10.11"
msgid ""
"Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, nayimāni aṅgārāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ "
"āpajjissantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Wouldn’t you know that those coals would not grow, increase, and spread?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.12"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. VAR: sāyanhasamayaṃ → sāyaṇhasamaye (s1-3) | sāyaṇhasamayaṃ (pts1) | sāyanhasamaye (mr)
msgctxt "an6.62:10.13"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi vā pana, ānanda, sāyanhasamayaṃ sūriye ogacchante, jāneyyāsi "
"tvaṃ, ānanda, āloko antaradhāyissati andhakāro pātubhavissatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Or suppose it was the late afternoon and the sun was going down. Wouldn’t "
"you know that the light was about to vanish and darkness appear?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.14"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

# See BB’s note. He follows reading abhidose, however this reading is repeated in the next case, where it is impossible. I follow texts’ abhido, and take it as an idiom meaning “not-divided from”, i.e. “right by”, “virtually”, “nearly”. This meaning not found in the dictionaries.
msgctxt "an6.62:10.15"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi vā, panānanda, abhido addharattaṃ bhattakālasamaye, jāneyyāsi "
"tvaṃ, ānanda, āloko antarahito andhakāro pātubhūto”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Or suppose that it’s nearly time for the midnight meal. Wouldn’t you know "
"that the light had vanished and the darkness appeared?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.16"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.17"
msgid ""
"“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand …"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.18"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:10.19"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:10.20"
msgid ""
"‘imassa kho puggalassa kusalā dhammā antarahitā, akusalā dhammā "
"sammukhībhūtā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:10.21"
msgid ""
"Atthi ca khvassa kusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tampi sabbena sabbaṃ samugghātaṃ "
"gacchati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:10.22"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ parihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "This person is still liable to decline in the future …"

msgctxt "an6.62:10.23"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisapuggalo cetasā ceto paricca vidito "
"hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:10.24"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"viditaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:10.25"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca "
"vidito hoti. (4)"
msgstr ""

