"viditaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:11.22"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca "
"vidito hoti. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:12.1"
msgid "Idha panāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.2"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand:"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.4"
msgid ""
"‘natthi imassa puggalassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattopi akusalo dhammo, "
"samannāgatoyaṃ puggalo ekantasukkehi anavajjehi dhammehi, diṭṭheva dhamme "
"parinibbāyissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person has not even a fraction of a hair’s tip of unskillful "
"qualities. They have exclusively bright, blameless qualities. They will "
"become extinguished in this very life.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, aṅgārāni sītāni nibbutāni sukkhe tiṇapuñje vā "
"kaṭṭhapuñje vā nikkhittāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that there were some cool, extinguished coals. They were placed on a "
"pile of grass or timber."

msgctxt "an6.62:12.6"
msgid ""
"Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, nayimāni aṅgārāni vuḍḍhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ "
"āpajjissantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Wouldn’t you know that those coals would not grow, increase, and spread?”"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.8"
msgid ""
"“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand …"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.9"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:12.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.62:12.11"
msgid ""
"‘natthi imassa puggalassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattopi akusalo dhammo, "
"samannāgatoyaṃ puggalo ekantasukkehi anavajjehi dhammehi, diṭṭheva dhamme "
"parinibbāyissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person has not even a fraction of a hair’s tip of unskillful "
"qualities. They have exclusively bright, blameless qualities. They will "
"become extinguished in this very life.’"

msgctxt "an6.62:12.12"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisapuggalo cetasā ceto paricca vidito "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"This is how another individual is known to the Realized One by comprehending "
"their mind."

msgctxt "an6.62:12.13"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"viditaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"And this is how the Realized One knows a person’s faculties by comprehending "
"their mind."

msgctxt "an6.62:12.14"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca "
"vidito hoti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"And this is how the Realized One knows the future origination of a person’s "
"qualities by comprehending their mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an6.62:13.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, ye te purimā tayo puggalā tesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ eko "
"aparihānadhammo, eko parihānadhammo, eko āpāyiko nerayiko."
msgstr ""
"And so, Ānanda, of the first three people one is not liable to decline, one "
"is liable to decline, and one is bound for a place of loss, hell."

msgctxt "an6.62:13.2"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, yeme pacchimā tayo puggalā imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ eko "
"parihānadhammo, eko aparihānadhammo, eko parinibbānadhammo”ti."
msgstr ""
"And of the second three people, one is liable to decline, one is not liable "
"to decline, and one is bound to become extinguished.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.62:13.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
